{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"alias":"evil-noble-soil","description":"The agent step-budget default is too low for the agentic plan-review VERIFIER, causing routine INDETERMINATE plan reviews on code-grounded tickets.\n\n## Why\n`DEFAULT_MAX_ITERATIONS = 25` (env `REBAR_LLM_MAX_STEPS`, src/rebar/llm/config.py:237) is too low for the agentic verifier (`plan-review-verifier-agentic`), which re-grounds findings against real code with tools. On code-grounded tickets it routinely exceeds 25 steps mid-verify â†’ the `verify` step fails â†’ the gate degrades to INDETERMINATE (`llm_unavailable`) â†’ no signed review â†’ the claim is blocked. Observed this cycle on `tarry-creep-range` (c38b): default 25 â†’ INDETERMINATE; `REBAR_LLM_MAX_STEPS=50` â†’ PASS + signed. Doubling the default to 50 removes the routine flake while staying well under the review-op floors that still apply.\n\n## What / files\n- `src/rebar/llm/config.py` â€” `DEFAULT_MAX_ITERATIONS` 25 â†’ 50, and refresh the env-doc comment (\"25 ~= 12 tool calls\" â†’ \"50 ~= 25 tool calls\").\n- `src/rebar/llm/completion.py`, `src/rebar/llm/code_review.py`, `src/rebar/llm/operations.py` â€” refresh the stale \"REBAR_LLM_MAX_STEPS=25 â‰ˆ 12 tool calls\" comments to the new default (the flooring to `_REVIEW_MIN_STEPS=120` / `_VERIFY_MIN_STEPS=240` is unchanged; the \"far too low for review\" sentiment still holds since 50 < 120).\n- `tests/unit/test_config_llm.py` â€” the default assertion `(16000, 25, 600)` â†’ `(16000, 50, 600)`.\n- `tests/interfaces/contracts/test_review_budget.py` â€” the `cfg.max_iterations == 25` preconditions â†’ `== 50` (the `>= _FLOOR` assertions stay valid since 50 < 120).\n\n## Scope\nIn: the default value + the stale doc/comment refresh + the two test updates. Out: the per-op floors (`_REVIEW_MIN_STEPS`/`_VERIFY_MIN_STEPS`), `max_tokens`, `timeout`.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `DEFAULT_MAX_ITERATIONS` is 50; `LLMConfig.from_env()` with no override yields `max_iterations == 50`.\n- [ ] The `REBAR_LLM_MAX_STEPS` env override and the `REBAR_LLM_MAX_ITERS` legacy alias still take precedence over the default (unchanged).\n- [ ] No doc/comment still claims the framework default is 25 (the stale \"=25 â‰ˆ 12 tool calls\" notes are refreshed).\n- [ ] The review/verify op floors (`_REVIEW_MIN_STEPS=120`, `_VERIFY_MIN_STEPS=240`) are unchanged and still applied above the new default.\n- [ ] `make check` + the suite pass (`test_config_llm` + `test_review_budget` updated).","id":"b2bb-2ac7-5ce3-4412","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"task","title":"Double the default LLM agent step budget (25 -> 50)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1782677227467447001,"uuid":"0c31769d-1ef4-4bde-89c2-bd3674b3dfa7"}